metadata.name: Dencity #10
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #185
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance

metadata.name: Light reverberations #64
metadata.description:
“The tinnitus like silence tearing the eardrums; a glare of darkness burned into the retina. “


As a visual & sound designer, my routine job is more related to new media installations, interactive programming design and lighting design. Explore to different luminaries and light sources, I gradually discover the relationship between light and sound waves. The role of reverberations are often sculptured the space when processing sounds, just like the lights play a similar role in 3D worlds. Reflections in the space make the sound more realistic, while the presence of light emphasis the dimensionality and depth of the space as well.

These scenes made of light and time remind me the painting and sculptures in the early 20th century, Futurism, which is characterized by technology, speed and violence. Umberto Boccioni and Gino Severini for instance. Nowadays, when we are free to deal with digital art beyond the existence of print or various archival forms, will it be an art movement called meta-futurism? Perhaps only things beyond our imagination can be called the future.

The project has been described during testing as being like picking up a camera that has fallen into space. It could be a collection of extreme brightness or endless darkness. If you decide to go into the space,  a carefully risk assessment is necessary.


Controls:

Click -> activate rotate control. (swipe gesture on mobile device)

Esc -> exit rotate and restart the rendering. (one tap on mobile device)

(Explore your own world by clicking on the canvas and rotate the viewpoint, tap “esc” to see the new result.)

The code used to calculate path tracing environment is from the three.js-PathTracing-Renderer ([https://github.com/erichlof/THREE.js-PathTracing-Renderer](https://github.com/erichlof/THREE.js-PathTracing-Renderer)), created by Erich Loftis.

metadata.name: HERE & NOW PORTALS #196
metadata.description:
The 'Portal' is your gateway to 'The Passage' created by HERE & NOW. This interactive minting project seeks to transform the traditional minting experience into something truly unique and unexpected.

Each 'Portal' gives you access and 1x reserve for all future 'The Passage' experiences both virtual and IRL.

For more information, visit hereandnow.events or join the discord, and join us in redefining what it means to mint.

See LICENCE.md for license details.

TECHNOLOGY :::::::::

This token is designed using a custom-built raymarching engine, built in a way that allows me to pass in chunks of GLSL code as determined by the params and features.

The geometry is generated using what's called a KIFS (Kaleidoscopic Iterated Function System) fractal, which involves taking the space, folding it, offsetting it, drawing in it, and repeating. By doing this, we can create some *very* complex appearing geometry using some relatively simple rules.

Finally, this is an intense simulation and requires a somewhat powerful GPU to properly be enjoyed.

CONTROLS :::::::::::

Mouse - Click and drag to move the camera around in the space.
Q/E - Roll the camera.
R/F - Change the speed of the camera.
SPACE - Stop the camera from moving.
O - Output a still picture without DOF.
P - Output a still picture with DOF.

URL PARAMS :::::::::

&still=true
This will just render a still image.

&dpr=X
Where X is a number. Will allow you to render the token to a higher or lower resolution

&fullscreen=true
Allows you to render the token at the screen resolution of your browser.

&width=X &height=Y
Allows you to set the specific dimensions of the token.

&dof=true
Turns fake depth of field on.

&doflenngth=X
Changes the length at with the DOF is calculated.

&steps=X
Allows you to explicitly set the number of steps the raymarcher can use.
